Job Description:
Job Description

DUTIES:

Collaborates with colleagues to build ways to streamline processes and efficiencies in order to generate financial benefits by growing revenue or reducing expenses;

Lead projects by developing project plans, setting timelines, keeping team members engaged and on track, and ensuring projects stay in scope and budget;

Act as data authority by working with the data, defining business rules, developing documentation, and by being a point of contact with for colleagues’ data questions and needs;

Maintain regular touch points with finance and commercial leadership to communicate project updates and share results with appropriate team members;

Validate and test data solutions from IT to ensure that they are accurate and that they meet requirements set forth by partners;

Define data-based business rules, build and maintain a repository with robust documentation for partners to reference;

Identify and address operational, financial, and technological risks to ensure little to no disruption in projects or day-to-day operations;

Develop training materials and presentations on data tools and new processes;

Build automated, financial reporting to replace manual reporting in order to streamline efforts and open up opportunities elsewhere in business.

REQUIREMENTS: Bachelor’s degree or foreign degree equivalent in Information Science, Information Technology, Computer Science, Finance, Mathematics, or a related field of study plus 5 years of experience in a business-facing IT organization, or related experience.

Must have experience or knowledge of:

Excel, Power BI, PowerPoint, Jira;

Tabular or multi-dimensional data models;

SQL;

Data warehousing and data modeling;

Project Management.

Travel: Willing to travel up to 10% domestic and international.
